hh3cIPsecMonitorV2.name: hh3cIPsecMonitorV2
hh3cIPsecMonitorV2.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Tech. Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cIPsecMonitorV2.description: The MIB is designed to get statistic information of IPsec tunnels. With this MIB, we can get information of a certain tunnel or all tunnels.

Hh3cIPsecDiffHellmanGrpV2.name: Hh3cIPsecDiffHellmanGrpV2
Hh3cIPsecDiffHellmanGrpV2.description: The Diffie Hellman Group used in the IKE and IPsec negotiations. invalidGroup(2147483647) is defined as invalid value.

Hh3cIPsecEncapModeV2.name: Hh3cIPsecEncapModeV2
Hh3cIPsecEncapModeV2.description: The encapsulation mode used by an IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. invalidMode(2147483647) is defined as invalid value.

Hh3cIPsecEncryptAlgoV2.name: Hh3cIPsecEncryptAlgoV2
Hh3cIPsecEncryptAlgoV2.description: The encryption algorithm used in the IKE and IPsec negotiations. invalidAlg(2147483647) is defined as invalid value.

Hh3cIPsecAuthAlgoV2.name: Hh3cIPsecAuthAlgoV2
Hh3cIPsecAuthAlgoV2.description: The authentication algorithm used in the IKE negotiations. invalidAlg(2147483647) is defined as invalid value.

Hh3cIPsecTrafficTypeV2.name: Hh3cIPsecTrafficTypeV2
Hh3cIPsecTrafficTypeV2.description: The type of the data flow.

Hh3cIPsecNegoTypeV2.name: Hh3cIPsecNegoTypeV2
Hh3cIPsecNegoTypeV2.description: The type of key used by an IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. invalidType(2147483647) is defined as invalid value.

hh3cIPsecTunnelV2Table.name: hh3cIPsecTunnelV2Table
hh3cIPsecTunnelV2Table.description: The IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel Table. There is one entry in this table for each active IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

hh3cIPsecTunIndexV2.name: hh3cIPsecTunIndexV2
hh3cIPsecTunIndexV2.description: The index of IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel Table. The value of the index is a number which begins at one and is incremented with each tunnel that is created. The value of this object will wrap at 2147483647.

hh3cIPsecTunIfIndexV2.name: hh3cIPsecTunIfIndexV2
hh3cIPsecTunIfIndexV2.description: The interface index( the ifIndex of ifTable ).

hh3cIPsecTunIKETunnelIndexV2.name: hh3cIPsecTunIKETunnelIndexV2
hh3cIPsecTunIKETunnelIndexV2.description: The index of the associated IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel (IKETunIndex in the IKETunnelTable). 2147483647 is defined as invalid value.

hh3cIPsecTunIKETunLocalIDTypeV2.name: hh3cIPsecTunIKETunLocalIDTypeV2
hh3cIPsecTunIKETunLocalIDTypeV2.description: The type of the local peer identity for the associated IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel (IKETunLocalType in the IKETunnelTable).

hh3cIPsecTunIKETunLocalIDVal1V2.name: hh3cIPsecTunIKETunLocalIDVal1V2
hh3cIPsecTunIKETunLocalIDVal1V2.description: The value of the local peer identity for the associated IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel (IKETunLocalValue1 in the IKETunnelTable). If the local peer type is ipv4Addr/ipv6Addr, this is the IP address used to identify the local peer. If the local peer type is ipv4AddrSubnet/ipv6AddrSubnet, this is the subnet address. If the local peer type is ipv4AddrRange/ipv6AddrRange, this is the beginning IP address of the range. If the local peer type is fqdn/userFqdn, this is the host name used to identify the local peer. If the local peer type is derAsn1Dn, this is the binary DER encoding of an ASN.1 X.500 Distinguished Name [X.501] of the principal whose certificates are being exchanged to establish the SA. If the local peer type is derAsn1Gn, this is the binary DER encoding of an ASN.1 X.500 GeneralName [X.509] of the principal whose certificates are being exchanged to establish the SA. If the local peer type is keyId, this is an opaque byte stream which may be used to pass vendor-specific information necessary to identify which pre-shared key should be used to authenticate Aggressive mode negotiations.

hh3cIPsecTunIKETunLocalIDVal2V2.name: hh3cIPsecTunIKETunLocalIDVal2V2
hh3cIPsecTunIKETunLocalIDVal2V2.description: The second specification of the local peer's IP address for the associated IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel (IKETunLocalValue2 in the IKETunnelTable). If the local peer type is ipv4AddrSubnet/ipv6AddrSubnet, this is the subnet mask. If the local peer type is ipv4AddrRange/ipv6AddrRange, this is the ending IP address of the range. If the local peer type is others, this is a zero-length string.

hh3cIPsecTunIKETunRemoteIDTypeV2.name: hh3cIPsecTunIKETunRemoteIDTypeV2
hh3cIPsecTunIKETunRemoteIDTypeV2.description: The type of the remote peer identity for the associated IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel (IKETunRemoteType in the IKETunnelTable).

hh3cIPsecTunIKETunRemoteIDVal1V2.name: hh3cIPsecTunIKETunRemoteIDVal1V2
hh3cIPsecTunIKETunRemoteIDVal1V2.description: The value of the remote peer identity for the associated IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel (IKETunRemoteValue1 in the IKETunnelTable). If the remote peer type is ipv4Addr/ipv6Addr, this is the IP address used to identify the remote peer. If the remote peer type is ipv4AddrSubnet/ipv6AddrSubnet, this is the subnet address. If the remote peer type is ipv4AddrRange/ipv6AddrRange, this is the beginning IP address of the range. If the remote peer type is fqdn/userFqdn, this is the host name used to identify the remote peer. If the remote peer type is derAsn1Dn, this is the binary DER encoding of an ASN.1 X.500 Distinguished Name [X.501] of the principal whose certificates are being exchanged to establish the SA. If the remote peer type is derAsn1Gn, this is the binary DER encoding of an ASN.1 X.500 GeneralName [X.509] of the principal whose certificates are being exchanged to establish the SA. If the remote peer type is keyId, this is an opaque byte stream which may be used to pass vendor-specific information necessary to identify which pre-shared key should be used to authenticate Aggressive mode negotiations.

hh3cIPsecTunIKETunRemoteIDVal2V2.name: hh3cIPsecTunIKETunRemoteIDVal2V2
hh3cIPsecTunIKETunRemoteIDVal2V2.description: The second specification of the remote peer's IP address for the associated IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel(IKETunRemoteValue2 in the IKETunnelTable). If the remote peer type is ipv4AddrSubnet/ipv6AddrSubnet, this is the subnet mask. If the remote peer type is ipv4AddrRange/ipv6AddrRange, this is the ending IP address of the range. If the remote peer type is others, this is a zero-length string.

hh3cIPsecTunLocalAddrTypeV2.name: hh3cIPsecTunLocalAddrTypeV2
hh3cIPsecTunLocalAddrTypeV2.description: The type of the IP address for the local peer of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

hh3cIPsecTunLocalAddrV2.name: hh3cIPsecTunLocalAddrV2
hh3cIPsecTunLocalAddrV2.description: The IP address of the local peer for the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

hh3cIPsecTunRemoteAddrTypeV2.name: hh3cIPsecTunRemoteAddrTypeV2
hh3cIPsecTunRemoteAddrTypeV2.description: The type of the IP address for the remote peer of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

hh3cIPsecTunRemoteAddrV2.name: hh3cIPsecTunRemoteAddrV2
hh3cIPsecTunRemoteAddrV2.description: The IP address of the remote peer for the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

hh3cIPsecTunKeyTypeV2.name: hh3cIPsecTunKeyTypeV2

hh3cIPsecTunEncapModeV2.name: hh3cIPsecTunEncapModeV2
hh3cIPsecTunEncapModeV2.description: The encapsulation mode used by the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

hh3cIPsecTunLifeSizeV2.description: The negotiated LifeSize of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel in kilobytes. 0 is defined as invalid value.

hh3cIPsecTunLifeTimeV2.description: The negotiated LifeTime of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel in seconds. 2147483647 is defined as invalid value.

hh3cIPsecTunRemainTimeV2.name: hh3cIPsecTunRemainTimeV2
hh3cIPsecTunRemainTimeV2.description: The remain time of SA in seconds. 2147483647 is defined as invalid value.

hh3cIPsecTunActiveTimeV2.name: hh3cIPsecTunActiveTimeV2
hh3cIPsecTunActiveTimeV2.description: The duration the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel has been active in hundredths of seconds. 2147483647 is defined as invalid value.

hh3cIPsecTunRemainSizeV2.name: hh3cIPsecTunRemainSizeV2
hh3cIPsecTunRemainSizeV2.description: The remain LifeSize of SA in kilobytes. 0 is defined as invalid value.

hh3cIPsecTunTotalRefreshesV2.name: hh3cIPsecTunTotalRefreshesV2
hh3cIPsecTunTotalRefreshesV2.description: The total number of security association refreshing performed.

hh3cIPsecTunCurrentSaInstancesV2.name: hh3cIPsecTunCurrentSaInstancesV2
hh3cIPsecTunCurrentSaInstancesV2.description: The number of security associations which are currently active or expiring.

hh3cIPsecTunInSaAhAuthAlgoV2.description: The authentication algorithm used by the inbound authentication header (AH) security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

hh3cIPsecTunInSaEspAuthAlgoV2.name: hh3cIPsecTunInSaEspAuthAlgoV2
hh3cIPsecTunInSaEspAuthAlgoV2.description: The authentication algorithm used by the inbound encapsulation security protocol(ESP) security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

hh3cIPsecTunDiffHellmanGrpV2.name: hh3cIPsecTunDiffHellmanGrpV2
hh3cIPsecTunDiffHellmanGrpV2.description: The Diffie Hellman Group used by the security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

hh3cIPsecTunOutSaEncryptAlgoV2.description: The encryption algorithm used by the outbound security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

hh3cIPsecTunOutSaAhAuthAlgoV2.name: hh3cIPsecTunOutSaAhAuthAlgoV2
hh3cIPsecTunOutSaAhAuthAlgoV2.description: The authentication algorithm used by the outbound authentication header (AH) security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

hh3cIPsecTunOutSaEspAuthAlgoV2.name: hh3cIPsecTunOutSaEspAuthAlgoV2
hh3cIPsecTunOutSaEspAuthAlgoV2.description: The authentication algorithm used by the outbound encapsulation security protocol(ESP) security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

hh3cIPsecTunPolicyNameV2.description: The policy name used by this IPsec tunnel.

hh3cIPsecTunStatusV2.name: hh3cIPsecTunStatusV2

hh3cIPsecTunnelStatV2Table.name: hh3cIPsecTunnelStatV2Table
hh3cIPsecTunnelStatV2Table.description: The IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel Statistics Table.

hh3cIPsecTunInOctetsV2.description: The total number of octets received by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated BEFORE determining whether or not the packet should be decompressed.

hh3cIPsecTunInDecompOctetsV2.description: The total number of decompressed octets received by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated AFTER the packet is decompressed.

hh3cIPsecTunOutPktsV2.description: The total number of packets sent by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.
